commentPostTextItems.html: England have held their nerve to pull off a three-wicket victory and level the series at 2-2. It was a match with several twist and turns.

Few would have given Pakistan a chance after they were restricted to 154 for 9. Then they hit back with three quick wickets before Pietersen chanced his arm and threatened to shut them out of the game. Afridi chipped in with two wickets in an over and Razzaq's dismissal of Read put Pakistan on top. However, Yardy's composure and Mahmood's deft hitting took England through to a well-earned victory.
Do stay with us for the post-match presentation. I'm done for the day and it's over to Jamie for the finishing touches. It's been fun bringing today's action to you. Cheers!

Thanks, George. Yeah, its been a match that kept us guessing. England held their nerve ultimately. Do check out out Andrew McGlashan's bulletin if you like in the meantime as we await the post-match presentation.
Well, we have it now - Sajid Mahmood gets the Man-of-the-Match award for his 2 for 24 and unbeaten 22. "It was a fantastic win" he says.

The Player of the Series, selected by the written media, goes to Younis Khan for his 201 runs at 53.75. "It was hard to bat first, we're disappointed," he says. "I'm glad for my form but it was disappointing to lose."
That's all we have for you, folks. I hope you've enjoyed our coverage of the entire series. This is Jamie saying good bye. Cheers!
